TAGGERMS downtime this weekend Cc All The Infrastructure group has requested downtime for TAGGERMS for maintenance purposes from pm CST Saturday November to am CST Sunday November If you have any questions or concerns please do not hesitate to contact me Thanks regards Karima Husain Project Manager Gas Tactical

FW New ERMS ApplicationPlease inform all ERMS RUNM users in your respective groups Thanks Karima Original Message From Lim Francis S Sent Friday August PM To DLTAGG ERMS User Support Cc DLTAGG ERMS Subject New ERMS Application in preparation for the upcoming Oracle i migration a new ERMS application has been developed THE OLD RUNM BLUE MENU WILL NO LONGER WORK when the database is upgraded to i What is different Most reports can be viewed on the screen using Adobe Acrobat Most reports and forms will now run on the PC and not on capers We have removed a lot of reports and forms that are no longer being used The screens now comes up faster A new report called curveviewer has been added to facilitate curve entry checking What is the same Your ERMS access ALL top page reports The Gas Daily Curve shift curveviewcurveloadbatchload program that runs on UNIX We will still provide you the old PortCalc and report screen that runs on the UNIX in case you do not like the PC version Attached is the documentation on how to start the new ERMSPC application You will have to close all of your PC applications and reboot your PC in order for the ERMSPC application to appear on your start menu Please inform all ERMS RUNM users

RUNM changes Cc All The RUNM application will be changed in the near future We urge all the users to please test the application by typing the following runmm to run it in production runmt to run it in egstest runmd to run it in egsdevel Please note that runm will eventually be replaced by runmm If you have any further questions or queries please do not hesitate to contact me at x or Francis Lim at x Thank you so much for your cooperation and support Regards Karima

Lee Kevin Alexander Kim D DLTAGG ERMS Brockhan Richard Subject ERMT migration to Oracle i postponed All The ERMT database migration to Oracle i has been postponed to Saturday August In the meantime we request you to please continue to test your production code on egsdevel Please test ALL your Excel and Access files and make sure that youre using the Oracle i driver for ODBC Attached please find the copy of the signoff form for the Oracle i upgrade If you havent done so already please send the signed form by Wednesday August via interoffice mail to my attention at EBD For users in Houston the floor support person will continue to check up in your areas to answer questions related to testing For users outside of Houston please contact us immediately via phone or email if you encounter any problems with your testing Thank you so much for your cooperation and support Best regards Karima Husain

FYI TAGGERMS environment Cc PST All FYI please note the following TAGGERMS environments and to which instance of Oracle they are pointing to TAGG Test is pointing to egsdevel egsdevel is an Oracle i instance TAGG Test launches as follows Start Programs Development Applications Test Applications TAGG TAGG Stage is pointing to egstest egstest is currently the existing Oracle instance TAGG Stage launches as follows Start Programs Development Applications Stage Applications TAGG TAGG Prod is pointing to the the current production database ERMT which is currently on Oracle TAGG Production launches as follows Start Programs Business Applications TAGG Thanks regards Karima Husain Project Manager TAGGERMS

Please read ERMS Reports Cc PST All In conjunction with the ongoing TAGGERMS database migration to Oracle i we are also converting our ERMS Reports to Oracle i Reports In regard to the Reports screen in ERMS launched from runm where ERMS reports like the TopPage Forwards and Options Detail are printed from could you please provide us a list of reports that you also print to FILE that is instead of printing the report to a printer you print the report to a file Please forward this to anyone in your group who is also using ERMS Reports If you have any questions or concerns please do not hesitate to contact either myself Francis Lim x or Jeremy Wong x Thanks regards Karima Husain x

Jennifer Fondren Mark Gillis Brian Giron Darron C Gossett Jeffrey C Groves Eric Hanson Kristen J Hernandez Nancy Keiser Kam Love Phillip M Mao Shari McIntyre Burton Moorer Torrey Nicoll Kenny Prejean Frank Reeves Kathy Stevens Martha Swinney John Tan Gladys Taylor Dimitri Torres Carlos Wlodarski Patryk McLaughlin Jr Errol Sharma Shifali Cc Lim Francis S Husain Karima Dang Ricky Dunsmore Ken Fortney Bill Greig Iain Hsieh Alex Krishnaswamy Jayant Lari Bryan Ma Felicia Ngo Toan Nolte Ron Swaim Michael Rivera Oscar Subject Changes in TAGG Deal Capture Screen Importance High We have a new version of TAGG Deal Capture Application under TAGGStage Following enhancements made in this version A new flag has been added in the deal capture screen that will allow a particular deal record to be identified as a component of a multilegged deal Requested by TAGG Deal Clearing Ron Nolte x Reason TAGG Deal Clearing has a process that sends confirmation related information to Commodity Logic However there are some TAGG deals that are made up of different legs In these cases Commodity Logic does not want to get any of the legs associated with multileg deals Please note that creating more than one leg for a deal does not mean that it is a multi legged deal Allow entry of negative price values in fixed price column of Deal Capture Application for SwapsForwardOptions only Requested by Victor Guggenheim Reason Negative Price Curve for Freight has been loaded into the system without any problem but user interfaceTAGG Deal Capture does not accept negative values The new version is planned to be migrated to production for July or If you encounter any problems please let me know Thunderball EOL bridge and TAGG Server and TDS system support personnel please verify if you are okay with change If you have any questions you can contact me x or Oscar X Regards Sanjeev X
